description:
The expected-graph.json golden fixture summary currently only captures totals and by-kind counts for nodes/edges. It does not capture the diff breakdown (modified / added / removed / unchanged), so regressions in classification of individual nodes and edges can slip through golden comparison unnoticed.

## Current shape

```json
{
  "plan_graph": {
    "nodes": {
      "total": 4,
      "by_kind": {
        "job": 1,
        "task": 3
      }
    },
    "edges": {
      "total": 3
    }
  },
  "resource_graph": {
    "nodes": {
      "total": 2,
      "by_kind": {
        "root": 1,
        "resource": 1
      }
    },
    "edges": {
      "total": 1,
      "dag": 1,
      "lateral": 0
    },
    "laterals": [],
    "phantoms": []
  }
}
```

## What we want

Add diff-state breakdowns for BOTH nodes and edges, in BOTH graphs. Shape sketch:

```json
{
  "plan_graph": {
    "nodes": {
      "total": 4,
      "by_kind": { "job": 1, "task": 3 },
      "by_diff_state": { "unchanged": 2, "modified": 1, "added": 1, "removed": 0 }
    },
    "edges": {
      "total": 3,
      "by_diff_state": { "unchanged": 2, "added": 1, "removed": 0 }
    }
  },
  "resource_graph": { "...same shape..." }
}
```

Exact field names to be decided during implementation — mirror whatever the JS graph builder emits (EdgeDiffState, DagNodeData.diffState).

## Why it matters

Today a regression that flips a node from `unchanged` to `modified` (or loses an `added` edge) won't be caught by golden comparison as long as totals stay the same. With diff-state counts in the summary, fixture regen (`just gen-expected`) becomes a much tighter regression net — especially for bugs in the drift/remote-only/no-op classification work (dagshund-15f7, dagshund-17pi, dagshund-24mn).

## Out of scope

- Per-node listings (would bloat the fixture). Summary counts only.
- Changing the graph builder itself — this is purely about the golden summary format.

## Follow-up

After the shape lands, all existing expected-graph.json goldens need regeneration: `just gen-expected --all` (review diff carefully before committing).
